<c:Tables>
<o:Table Id="o87">
<a:ObjectID>1EB1D973-F4A9-4CD5-BCA0-32B1EE2F840E</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Segmentation Type</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSEGTYPE</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>1366027527</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>FRXA567</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1729071305</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>frxb406</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>This table contains the definition of each supported Segmentation Type.
Any Segmentation defined in the Omega 2.0 system should refer to a registered Segmentation Type, which induces a set of global common characteristics.
Only active Segmentation Types are actually processed by the Omega 2.0 system.
</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\nouicompat\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Riched20 10.0.19041}\viewkind4\uc1 
\pard\b\f0\fs20 2024-10-16: Retro T&amp;S Initiatives, Non Proportionnal Retrocession Plan\b0\par
2 new columns are added in TSEGTYPE\par
- the Retro Underwriting Year - RTY_NF\par
- the Segmentation Mode - SGTTYPMOD_NT\par
\par
\par
2013-05-29 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- Creation\par
\par
2013-06-17 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- last update fields become mandatory\par
- changed the GRPLVL_B boolean field into a GRPLVL_CT codification one to support more management cases.\par
- added the UWABSTRACT_B field to track segmentations required for UW Abstract export.\par
\par
2013-06-25 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- remove EVALORD_NT field to define the order which Segmentation Types are evaluated in production. \par
-Update banalised codifications\par
\par
2013-07-01 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- Rename GRPLVL_CT to SGTMGTLVL_CT\par
}
</a:Description>
