<o:Table Id="o97">
<a:ObjectID>C1A00CCA-18EB-4A15-9855-A3B80D3FC856</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Segmentation Evaluation Requests</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSEGRUNSCHED</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>1366103777</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>FRXA567</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1380906909</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>FRXB156</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>This table contains the Segmentation operations asked by Omega 2.0 Users (i.e. not those implicitely triggered by the daily SEG batch based on the frequencies configured in the TSEGMENTATION table.
A user may indeed manually request for a Segmentation evaluation (in full or delta mode), or for a Snapshot at additional schedules than the default configured ones.
Max one request may be created per Segmentation on a scheduled date: the current active version of the Segmentation is considered at execution time and, in case of group level Segmentation (covering the 3 production sites), the same request is processed by the 3 batch nights on their respective portfolio scope. 
These requests are retrieved automatically by the daily SEG batch and included it its execution plan. Manual entries supersede default configured ones in the batch execution : e.g. if the default Segmentation configuration indicates a delta evaluation for a Segmentation and a full evaluation is requested, a full execution is done.
Requests may be modified/deleted as long as they have not started to be processed (based on status).
Beware that &quot;Simulation Requests&quot; are not managed via this scheduling table (but standard asynchronous jobs in the BTEC database).
</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2510;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 2013-05-29 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- Creation\par
\par
2013-06-17 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- last update fields become mandatory\par
\par
2013-06-25 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
-Update banalised codifications\par
}
</a:Description>
