<o:Table Id="o98">
<a:ObjectID>0D678065-61C3-4A75-BD00-C766E3BBE6B7</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Segmentation Exception</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSEGMENTEXCEPT</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>1366123553</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>FRXA567</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1380905224</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>FRXB156</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>This table contains all exceptions for a given Segmentation.
It defines, for a given portfolio element (Contract, Section, Placement, depending on the Segmentation scope and granularity), the Segment to be assigned regardless of Segment Rules evaluations.
These exception are usually set by Segmentation administrators when encountering errors at segmentation evaluation (e.g. elements assigned to multiple Segments, very specific cases not included in the Rule criteria...).</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
